Yesterday in WK, there was something very strange. A nameless corpse was jumping around near one of the groups of bandits. Above it's head were the words &quot;'s corpse&quot;. If you walked too close, it spammed you with constant broadcasts of:<br>
<br>
&quot; died.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sometimes, occasionally, it would say that it's comrades would avenge its death.<br>
<br>
Being the curious person that I am, I petitioned a GM about it. Mr. GM came over to check it out, and decided to get out his invisible tools which give out corpse info.<br>
<br>
And the zone crashed.<br>
<br>
So there you have it. How to get a GM to crash a zone. Strange nameless jumping corpse required. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=660066><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub22.ezboard.com/uillmizzo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>illmizzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I got banned from Flowers <br> boards and all I got was <br> this lousy title.</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(6/19/02 11:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumstupidcharactertricks.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to make a GM crash a zone......</span><hr size=1> i saw that stuff over at highhold or somewhere on the way one time.. i kept trying to kill it... nothing would work <p>Do it Ted, amputate..Make it pay for its mistakes...<BR>

